article.headline: Boise State 83, Elon University 67
article.story: BOISE, Idaho (AP) -- Eric Lane scored 21 points, all on 3-pointers, and Jermaine Blackburn added 18 to lift Boise State over Elon 83-67 Tuesday night. Five Bronco players scored in double figures, as the team shot 59 percent from the field and 16 of 30 from 3-point range. Franco Harris scored 13, and Seth Robinson and Coby Karl added 12 points each. Elon (2-9) led 52-51 with 13:2l left when Boise State went on a 3-point tear, hitting six in a row and building a 69-56 lead with 7:53 left. Rasmi Gamble led Elon with 16 points, while LeVonn Jordan chipped in 10. The Phoenix hit 50 percent from the field, but only 3 for 10 from 3-point range. Boise State (6-4) played without leading scorer and rebounder Jason Ellis, who played the game's first minute, but sat out the rest with a back injury.
